{
  "text": "To further investigate the function of CSI1 protein domains, we assessed the subcellular localization of YFP-tagged CSI1 truncations in transgenic Arabidopsis seedlings. Each of the YFP-tagged CSI1 truncations was driven by the 35S promoter. Their localization could be classified into three different types: intracellular diffuse signals (CSI1 1-2013 , CSI1 1-998 , and CSI1 1-577 ), PM-localized signals (CSI1 997-2150 and CSI1 1738-2150 ), or distinct puncta at the cell cortex (CSI1 2012-2150 ; Figure 1C ). The localization of CSI1 997-2150 and CSI1 1738-2150 appeared to be identical; therefore, YFP-CSI1 1738-2150 was used for further analysis. Twenty minutes of exposure to FM4-64, a membrane-impermeable fluorescent lipid dye, was used to label the PM to determine the focal plane of YFP-CSI1 1738-2150 and YFP-CSI1 2012-2150 [CITATION_1] . YFP-CSI1 1738-2150 colocalized with FM4-64 at the focal plane of the PM, whereas YFP-CSI1 2012-2150 localized to puncta adjacent to the PM at the cell cortex (Supplemental Figure  3) . YFP-CSI1 1738-2150 localized with a uniform distribution at the PM, with the exception of multiple linear stripes that lacked fluorescence and were reminiscent of cortical microtubules. To verify the identity of these stripes, we generated Arabidopsis seedlings coexpressing CFP-TUA1 (ALPHA-1 TUBULIN) and YFP-CSI1 . CFP-TUA1 labeled the stripes that were devoid of YFP-CSI1 1738-2150 signal ( Figure 1D ; Supplemental Movie 1). Furthermore, treatment with oryzalin, a microtubule depolymerization reagent, removed the stripes, which resulted in a uniform distribution of YFP-CSI1 1738-2150 at the PM ( Figure 1D ). In contrast, YFP-CSI1 2012 -2150 , which is representative of the CSI1 C2 domain, localized to small cortical compartments along linear tracks that were reminiscent of cortical microtubules ( Figure 1C ). In the Arabidopsis seedlings coexpressing mCherry-TUA5 and YFP-CSI1 2012-2150 , YFP-CSI1 2012-2150 colocalized with cortical microtubules extensively (Supplemental Movie 2). Oryzalin treatment depleted most of the cortical YFP-CSI1 2012-2150 punctate signals, suggesting that the particles were connected with the cortical microtubules ( Figure 1E ; Supplemental Movie 3). Therefore, the in vivo localization of both YFP-CSI1 1738 -2150 and YFP-CSI1 2012 -2150 is influenced by cortical microtubules.",
  "correct_citation": {
